overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request riddled with
  issues, including critical security flaws, functional bugs, and failing Vercel
  deployments. The agent systematically tackled these problems, starting with
  lint errors and moving to more complex security vulnerabilities like forgeable
  authentication cookies, which were resolved by implementing HMAC-signed
  sessions using the Web Crypto API for Edge Runtime compatibility. Functional
  bugs in PDF generation (NaN values, minute calculations, hardcoded user
  names), form field handling (null values), and API pagination were also
  addressed. A significant hurdle was the persistent Vercel deployment failure,
  which was ultimately traced to a missing database URL configuration in the
  Prisma schema. After fixing this, all checks passed, and the PR was ready.
